    Patch 0.16.5 is live

    By: Egerod, 06-06-2020

    Edit: MAL blocked the endpoint I was using to syncronize with them, MAL have therefor been disabled again. If you use MAL, I suggest exporting your list AniList and syncing up using them instead, this can be done quick and easy by following this guide.

    Bug fixing patch, fixing the MAL integration bug from yesterdays patch.

    Patch Notes
    Changes:
    Updated the registration and guest registration page layouts, so that the MyAnimeList field is now positioned correctly.
    MAL list updating is now rate limited (due to limits from MAL), updating your MAL list might therefore take up to a minute or two depending on the load, but should in general update quickly.
    Bug Fixes:
    Fixed a bug causing MAL integration wouldn't update the entire list.
    Fixed a bug where some players without MAL accounts got the wrong shows set as watched.
    Fixed a bug where players where guest accounts where able to open the leaderboard, resulting in an error.
    Fixed a bug where you could try to invite players when playing solo, this would result in an error.
    Fixed a bug where trying to join ranked matches on a guest account would result in a soft lock.
    Fixed a bug where players could send friend requests to guest accounts, with guest account can't accept.

    Card Game Boy Wins the 16th Avatar Drive and Patch 0.16.4 is live

    By: Egerod, 05-06-2020

    With a last second donation "Card Game Boy" have managed to win the 16th avatar drive, and have been added to the list of planned avatars!

    Patch Notes
    New Features:
    Guest accounts have been added to the game. It's now possible for new players to try out the game without registering by creating a guest account. Guest account have limited access, and can't use features such as the chat, host multiplayer games or participate in ranked and are deleted ones the player closes the game. Guest accounts can be upgraded to full accounts any time doing play by completing the registration process.
    It's now possible to host a solo games that doesn't show up in the room browser.
    Changes:
    The verify account page have been updated, should solve an issue with new players not getting the confirmation that the account have been verified.
    The main menu play button have been split into a multiplayer (takes you to the room browser) and solo button (lets you setup a solo game). MyAnimeList is supported as a list host ones again.

    Expand Library FAQ

    What video hosts does the game support?

    What version of a song should I use?

    Can I use a still image instead of the video?

    What should be included in the video?

    What file formats are accepted?

    What are the quality requirements?

    What are keyframes?

    What happens once my file has been submitted?

    What songs are shown in the Expand Library?

    A song is missing from the database, how do I get it added?

    My upload was rejected but I didnt get a message?

    Im not sure what to do to get my upload approved?

    What video hosts does the game support?

    The game supports the open host Catbox and the closed hosts Animethemes and Openings.moe.
    The open hosts allows anyone to upload and share files on them, while the closed hosts doesn't allow users to upload, but already have a large library of videos.

    What version of a song should I use?

    You should always use the version that was used in the show. For openings and endings thats usually the 1.30 minute cut version. In the case that different versions are used throughout the show, you should go with the one most commonly used, if theyre used equally for with the first one.

    Can I use a still image instead of the video?

    For openings/endings you should always use the actual video.
    For insert songs video versions (with potential background noise/talk edited out) is strongly preferred, but still image versions might get approved until an edited version becomes available.

    What should be included in the video?

    The opening/ending/scene the song plays in.
    If a song plays with talking or other sounds during the scene, replace the audio with an identical clean version.

    What file formats are accepted?

    Video files should be in webm format, and sound files in mp3. Any other formats will be rejected by the scan bot.

    What are the quality requirements?

    The song must not be pitched, sped up, slowed down or remixed in any way from their original versions. Any silence at the start or end of the song should be cut out. Likewise, extended notes at the end of the song should be cut short.
    The video should also be of decent quality and not contain hardsubs, through exceptions can be made for older or rare shows where a better quality isnt available.

    What are keyframes?

    Keyframes are special frames set when the video is encoded. They allow for skipping in the video without having to load the rest of the video up to the point skipped to.
    For AMQ a minimum of 1 keyframe for each 10 seconds of video is required, anything less will get rejected by the bot. Its recommended to have 1 keyframe per 5 second.

    What happens once my file has been submitted?

    After your song have been submitted, itll enter the queue to be scanned by the scan bot. The scan bots checks if the encoding, resolution and keyframe count of the file are correct. If the file is already approved on another host, the bot will automatically approve the upload or else itll pass it to the moderator team, who will validate that the song is correct and check the quality of the video.
    If your song is rejected, youll receive a server message about it and the Notes + xp rewarded for the upload are removed.

    What songs are shown in the Expand Library?

    The Expand Library shows all songs currently in the database for anime that are in your linked lists, so long as they do not have mp3, 480, 720p qualities up on catbox, along with a link to the uploads on animethemes and openings.moe (if available). Additionally if a song is in the approval queue and has no other qualities uploaded, it will not appear in the expand library either.

    A song is missing from the database, how do I get it added?

    First make sure the song isnt already in the database: Doesnt appear in the Expand Library or in game (do a solo quiz with only that songs show in your list).
    If it wasnt in the Expand Library or in game, you can request to have it added on the games Discord. Make sure to read the FAQ channel and pins in the #database-fixes channel, for how to request it.

    My upload was rejected but I didnt get a message?

    Theres a bug in the update system that causes some rejection messages not be send out. If you have any questions about why your upload got rejected, you can ask the database moderators in the games Discord.

    Im not sure what to do to get my upload approved?

    If your upload got rejected, or youre not sure how to get a upload approved, you can contact the database mods on the games Discord, who will be able to help you.

    Last Man Standing Rules

    In Last Man Standing each players start with 1-5 lives (depending on game settings).

    To win, you have to be the last player remaining alive

    If a living player answers correctly, all other living players who didn't guess correctly losses one life

    When you die, the game isnt over. For each song you answer correctly after dying youll earn a respawn point, and if you manage to collect 3 respawn points, you'll respawn back into the fight! But if you get a song wrong, youll lose all your respawn points.
    Finally, to get the third and last respawn point, you must not only guess the song correctly, but all living players must get it wrong as well.

    Battle Royale Rules

    In Battle Royale, the game has an added loot phase

    In the loot phase, players first chose a drop point on the map, and then move around collecting anime. Ones the loot phase is over, a Last Man Standing quiz is started, with only songs from the anime collected in the loot phase

    In the loot phase, you chose a drop point by clicking a tile on the map. After dropping you can move around with WASD or arrow keys, and collect anime scattered around the map by clicking on them ones you get close to them

    Data Stores are also scattered around the map, and contain several anime, but can first be opened ones you get close to them

    You can change between map tiles by standing on the gates at the edge of the tiles and clicking on them

                      FAQ

                      What is the Avatar Drive?

                      The Avatar Drive is your way to support the game, while at the same time influencing what the future avatars will be. The system is pretty straightforward, when donating you can chose to donate towards any avatar in the Avatar Drive or nominate a new avatar. The value donated is then added to that avatars score.
                      When the time comes to add a new avatar to the game, whoever is leading the Avatar Drive is chosen.

                      What Type of Avatars Can I Nominate?

                      You can nominate any type of avatar you can think of, as long as they are not offensive, can legally be added to the game and fits into the design of the game. All entries are reviewed by an admin, and we do reserve the right to refuse nominations that doesnt follow the above mentioned guidelines.
                      You are also allowed to nominate other artists original characters, but they will only be added to the drive if the artist agrees to their character appearing in the game.

                      Can I Nominate an Existing Avatar Again?

                      You are more than welcome to nominate an existing avatar for the Avatar Drive. If an existing avatar win the drive, new skins and/or poses will be added to that avatar. You are also more than welcome to specify what you want the skin to be, let's say you want to give Hibiki a ninja outfit, you can nominate Ninja Hibiki.

                      When Are New Avatars Added to the Game?

                      A new avatar is added to the game once the drive has raised enough money to cover the production cost of adding the avatar and running the game. This value can vary depending on the length of the drive. Calculating the length of the drive and the amount to be raised will be worked out after the first couple of drives. Based on the experience we will add a clear goal to be reached for a new avatar to be added! The goal is to have a new avatar enter the game every 1-2 months.

                      Ranked Mode

                      Challenge yourself against your friends and the AMQ community by joining the daily ranked game. Each ranked game will earn you ranked points, unlocking new exclusive rewards and getting you closer to join the best of the best in the region championship hosted at the end of each month.

                      How it Works

                      Regions

                      The ranked mode is split up into two separate regions, each with their own leaderboard, start time and championship. You will be able to participate in both regions, but ranked points only counts for the region in which they're earned in. The two regions can be seen below.

                      West
                      Covering NA/SA
                      Start Time
                      20:30 CDT/CST
                      Central
                      Covering EU
                      Start Time
                      20:30 CET/CEST

                      Ranked Game

                      Each day 30 minutes before start time you will be able to join the ranked lobby from the main menu. The ranked game allows for an unlimited amount of players to join and will run for 80 songs. The 80 songs will be selected at random following the distribution to the right

                      At the end of each ranked game, you'll earn ranked points in the following way:
                      10 points for guessing at least one song.
                      Points equal to the percent of players beaten (not including top 50 if there's more than a 100 players in the match).
                      Bonus point for getting top 40. Earning 5 points for each spot above 41, 10 for each above 9 and 30 for being first. Meaning 40th get 5, 2nd 230 and 1st 260 bonus points.

                      Song Types

                      28 Openings
                      14 Endings
                      10 Insert
                      23 Random

                      Minimum Guess Rate

                      5 - 40%+
                      10 - 35%+
                      10 - 30%+
                      10 - 25%+
                      5 - 15%+
                      35 - 0%+

                      End of Season

                      The last Saturday of each month, instead of the normal ranked game, a championship game is hosted instead. The championship games functions like a normal ranked game, except only the top 150 players in the region are able to participate, with the winner earning the title of Region Champion.

                      The Monday after the championship, all ranked points are reset and a new season starts.

                      Rewards

                      At the end of the season you'll be awarded badges* based on tier you reached. Tiers are based on the amount of ranked points you earned in the season. The different tiers can be seen below.

                      • 0
                      • 250
                      • 500
                      • 750
                      • 1000
                      • - Bronze
                      • - Silver
                      • - Gold
                      • - Platinum
                      • - Diamond

                      The top 3 players of each region championship will be awarded unique badges

                      *Badges are a new type of rewards you'll be able to display in game. They will be added in the coming months and will be awarded retroactively

                      Rules

                      The ranked game mode is a test of individual skills, it's therefore important that you doesnt hint or share answers with other players. All tools, methods or software that gives an unfair advantage is banned as well (as it is for all game modes).
                      Breaking the above rules can result in your account getting banned and all ranked rewards removed.

                      Guidelines

                      Anime Music Quiz is meant to be fair and enjoyable for everyone. To ensure this its important you follow the below guidelines, as well as any instructions from moderators. Failure to follow these guidelines will resolve in chat or game bans depending on the case.

                      Dont Cheat

                      Using any type of external software or tool that gives an unfair advantage is considered cheating. This in general covers, but is not limited to tools that reveal extra information about the song, video or show.

                      No Teaming in Ranked

                      Ranked is meant to be a test of individual skill, teaming or sharing answers with other players is therefore strictly prohibited. Outside of ranked you are more than welcome to share answers with friends if the hosts of the room are okay with it, but keep the sharing out of ranked.

                      No (Semi-)Automated Grind

                      Its okay to grind for notes and tickets as long as you put in the work for it. But using any tools to automate or semi automate the grind is strictly against the rules, and will resolve in a perma ban if caught.

                      Dont Harass Other Players

                      The game is for everyone, so harassment of others is not tolerated. Its of course okay to banter between friends, but make sure everyone is in on it.

                      No Hate Speech or Racism

                      This goes without saying, be nice to each other and dont go throwing around racial slurs.

                      Ticket System

                      The Ticket System allows players to spend tickets to unlock exclusive recolors/edits, skins and emote/profile-images.

                      How to Earn Tickets

                      Players receive one ticket each time they level up, with a bonus 5 tickets every 10th level. Tickets can also be brought directly or be earned by backing the games Patreon.

                      How does Rolls Work

                      You can spend tickets to roll for exclusive rewards in the ticket system. Each roll costs 2 tickets. Rewards are split into 4 rarities, with different chances of being rolled:

                      85% chance: Simple skin recolors and Emote/Profile-Images.

                      10% chance: Advanced skin recolors.

                      4.5% chance: Major skin recolors and current seasonal skins.

                      0.5% chance: Advanced exclusive skins.

                      Reward recolors for a reward skin cant be rolled until the skin has been unlocked. For non reward skins, the reward recolors can be unlocked without unlocking the skin first.

                      How does Rhythm Work

                      If you roll a duplicate of a reward already unlocked youll instead earn an amount of rhythm based on the rewards rarity. Rhythm can then be spend to unlock any specific reward item ones enough of it has been collected.
